<br>
/rs inc %t (for raid pulling)<br>
/g inc %t (for group pulling<br>
/pet attack (for swarm kiting)<br>
/pet target(for swarm kiting)<br>
<br>
Thats just an example btw.<br>
<br>
The main point being that if you can stand the spam once a minute or so on *that command is illegal* messages, then you can have one hotkey take up the same number of hotkeys it would take 3-4 to have otherwise.<br>
<br>
when soloing the /rs and /g will give error messages and do nothing, then the rest of the key will take effect and do the intended swarm kiting function, and so on.<br>
<br>
when you are raiding you probably wont have a pet, so that command will do nothing, etc.<br>
<br>
when exping in a group the /rs and /pet commands most likely wont be useable...<br>
<br>
